# environments.map — host-side branch -> environment map (OPERATOR-owned, trusted).
# Install as $RUNNER_BASE/etc/environments.map (or point CICD_ENV_MAP at it in runner.conf).
# Lines: <repo-glob>  <branch-glob>  <env>    First match wins. '#' = comment.
#
# Purpose: the runner resolves a run's ENVIRONMENT from its (trusted, gitolite-gated)
# BRANCH, then decrypts ONLY ci/secrets.<env>.enc.yaml. The branch->env binding lives
# HERE (host-side), NOT in the pushed .gitolite/ci.yml, so a pusher cannot claim another
# tier's secrets. This file is the equivalent of GitHub "environment protection rules".
#
# If NO map is present, env defaults to the sanitized branch name (dev->dev, prod->prod).
# Only add entries to ALIAS a branch whose name differs from its env (e.g. main->prod).

# repo-glob        branch-glob     env
# tovasol/*        main            prod
# tovasol/*        release/*       prod
# tovasol/*        staging         qa
